subject: resource/Stomach
object: The stomach is a muscular, hollow, dilated part of the digestive system which functions as an important organ of the digestive tract in many animals, including vertebrates, echinoderms, insects (mid-gut), and molluscs. It is involved in the second phase of digestion, following mastication (chewing).In most vertebrates, the stomach is located between the esophagus and the small intestine.
